Crypto has really opened my eyes to the financial risks that are hidden in plain sight in our day to day lives.

The learnings gained here help you question everything, and that takeaway alone is worth onboarding the world.

When I first opened a bank account I do not remember many structured products being advertised, but all it is nowadays is structured deposits and FX. 

Gotten awfully complex in a very short amount of time.

There are so many financial products nowadays that allow you to pick your own risk/reward balance.

DC pension plans, insurance plans, etc.

It hit me today that this is just an act of outsourcing. In a world of little to no growth, it's on you to find your ROI.

I believe there is a nontrivial likelihood that how a jurisdiction handles crypto regulation and taxation will drive migrations across countries.

Time will tell.

(Wake up Japan)

It is easy to say that you will hodl and not sell, but in some jurisdictions tax liabilities arise when any exchange happens, even crypto-crypto or crypto-NFT.

A taxable event will occur sooner or later. Reliable off ramps to fiat are essential to cover tax liabilities.
